mt_samples %>%
  unnest_tokens(word, transcription) %>%
  count(word,sort = TRUE) %>%
  top_n(20,n) %>%
  ggplot(aes(x= reorder(word, n), y=n)) +
  geom_col() +
  coord_flip() +
  labs(x = "Word", y = "Count", title = "Top 20 Most Frequent Words")

Explaination:The âwordâ is the most frequent word, and that make senses because words likeâthe and wasâ is really the word that we usually use.
